res in milliseconds [INDEX]!Let's execute Step 1: Setting up the OSPF Architecture parameters.🏛️ The OSPF Blueprint ProtocolFor this enterprise tier, we are going to run OSPF Process ID 1 inside Area 0 (The Backbone) [INDEX]. Every single router and core switch will participate [INDEX].To make OSPF perfectly clean, we will give each device a unique Router ID (its digital name tag) [INDEX]:Toronto Edge Router (YYZ-BR-RTR-01): 1.1.1.1 [INDEX]Toronto Core Switch (YYZ-BR-CS-01): 2.2.2.2 [INDEX]New York Edge Router (NYC-HQ-RTR-01): 3.3.3.3 [INDEX]New York Core Switch (NYC-HQ-CS-01): 4.4.4.4 [INDEX]🛠️ Step 2: Igniting OSPF on the Toronto Edge RouterWe must tell the router to advertise its internal transit networks down to the switch, but we never want it to blast OSPF routing updates out of its public internet port (Gig0/2) [INDEX]!Open the CLI of your Toronto Edge Router (YYZ-BR-RTR-01) and inject your very first dynamic routing process:textYYZ-BR-RTR-01# configure terminal

