ting at Priority 1, this first step resulted in a complete tie [INDEX].🥈 Tiebreaker 2: The Router ID (The Highest Number Wins!)When the priority ties, the OSPF engine falls back to a basic mathematical comparison: The device with the highest numerical Router ID wins the election and becomes the DR [INDEX]!Let’s look at the digital name tags we assigned them:Toronto Edge Router: 1.1.1.1 [INDEX]Toronto Core Switch: 2.2.2.2 [INDEX]Since 2.2.2.2 is mathematically higher than 1.1.1.1, the Core Switch won the election and took the DR crown, forcing your Edge Router to settle for the BDR position [INDEX]!🏛️ Real-World Architect Note: Who Should Be the Leader?In a true production data center design, a senior network architect will usually override this default election [INDEX].We prefer the Edge Router to be the DR because it acts as the centralized gateway out to the WAN and the public internet, and its CPU is dedicated strictly to packet routing paths [INDEX].If you ever want to change the election so the Router wins, you don't change its ID—you just go into the Router's interface port and set its OSPF priority higher than 1 (e.g., ip ospf priority 255) [INDEX]!🛑 Stop Right HereLet that election logic soak in completely. For the CCNA exam, remembering "Highest Router ID wins the tiebreaker" is an absolute mandatory point [INDEX].Now that the local Toronto cluster is processing dynamically, let's wire up the other side of the country.Are you ready to jump onto your New York Edge Router and Core Switch to activate their local OSPF processes (3.3.3.3 and 4.4.4.4), or do you want to review how we cross the cross-country VPN link using OSPF [INDEX]? Tell me where we strike next, partner!10 sitesOSPF DR/BDR Election explained - Page 6 - Lessons DiscussionDec 20, 2016 — This is because the technology being used to connect them (Ethernet) is by definition a multi access technology, allowing for mult...NetworkLessons.comOSPF DR and BDR - NetworkingMar 25, 2021 — OSPF will automati